SUMMARY:Lunchtime Discovery:  Conservation and Access to the Outdoors
DESCRIPTION:Join us in-person in the SECU Daily Planet Theater or watch the livestream on YouTube. \nAccess to land for agriculture\, education\, and recreation is an increasing challenge in the Triangle. Kierra will explore how conservation land trusts can provide innovative solutions to protect and expand land access. We’ll also look at the partnerships needed to make these solutions possible. \nKierra Hyman\, Good Ground Manager at Triangle Land Conservancy \n\nThroughout the month of March\, the Lunchtime Discovery Series will recognize Women’s History Month and women’s contributions to science and conservation. These live virtual presentations will be held each Wednesday from noon to 1:00 p.m. and are hosted by the NC Museum of Natural Sciences Coordinator of Current Science Programs Chris Smith. Brought to you by the NC DEQ Office of Environmental Education and Public Affairs and the NC Museum of Natural Sciences. \n﻿﻿
URL:https://naturalsciences.org/calendar/event/lunchtime-discovery-the-adaptable-human-human-anatomy-in-the-extremes-2/
LOCATION:Nature Research Center\, 121 West Jones Street\, Raleigh\, NC\, 27601\, United States
CATEGORIES:Adults,Discussions,Educators,General Events,K-12 Students,Lectures,Lunchtime Discovery,Teens,Virtual
ORGANIZER;CN="Chris%20Smith":MAILTO:christopher.smith@naturalsciences.org
