SUMMARY:Nature Stories
DESCRIPTION:Join us as we open your eyes to the wonderful world of nature through a family-friendly\, nature-filled storytime. We’ll begin by sharing a story in the Nature PlaySpace Amphitheater at 10:30am\, and will then head to other areas of Prairie Ridge as we explore natural themes from each day’s stories in a hands-on\, interactive manner. \nThis is a free program beginning at 10:30am. Come dressed for the weather and prepared to take a walk! Most walks will be stroller friendly. Everyone is welcome at the Nature PlaySpace\, but it has been designed especially for kids 7 and younger.  Nature Stories books and activities were chosen with this age group in mind. \nPlease note that this program occurs at the Museum’s Prairie Ridge Ecostation location in west Raleigh. For more information\, contact prairieridge@naturalsciences.org
URL:https://naturalsciences.org/calendar/event/nature-stories-4/2026-03-12/
LOCATION:Prairie Ridge\, 1671 Gold Star Drive\, Raleigh\, NC\, 27607\, United States
CATEGORIES:Children,Nature Stories,Outdoor Experiences
